Two former chiefs of South Korea's state intelligence agency were to be arraigned in court Tuesday on charges they oversaw the agency's illegal wiretapping of phone conversations of influential figures.
Lim Dong-won, 71, and Shin Gunn, 64, headed the National Intelligence Service successively between December 1999 and April 2003 under former President Kim Dae-jung.
Prosecutors said former President Kim wasn't involved and that the two ex-chiefs had ignored Kim's instruction to end illegal wiretapping.
Both Lee and Shin denied the charges at court appearances Tuesday.
